60th High Priest of Midnight Fury <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ulaoke.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Laoke</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 1270<br> <font color=#E9D756>(5/31/02 6:07:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9801.topic&index=28>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How do YOU solo?</span><hr size=1> How do I solo?  Very well indeed, thanks : )<br>
<br>
  On a slightly less whimisical note, monk soloing is easy.  Grab a XP giving mob that you can take down, pull it to a location you can fight without adds (unless adds just mean more XP) and beat it down.  Hit Mend as soon as possible in the fight so that it recycles as fast as possible (I typically hit it when I get down to 3 bubbles of health), instill doubt to fear the mob if you have the space to fear kite.<br>
<br>
  Use stone stance discipline as it resets the fastest and can be a real boon to XPing if you have it.  Once the mob is dead, bind wound as high as you can and move on to the next mob.  As our Bind wound cap is 200 pre-50 and we can get to 201 &amp; 70% binding at 51st level, our downtime is slight compared to other melee classes.<br>
<br>
  Monks with their epic for spell haste, a haste item &amp; fungi tunics can take down XP mobs as fast as anyone soloing.  A very well equipped monk has virtually no downtime taking XP mobs down if she hits the right mobs:  I can quite easily do Velketor spiders for example almost indefinitely.<br>
<br>
  Monks can avoid bad pulls &amp; trains through feign death, which means they can solo in areas that would be suicide for another class.  Mend is a huge asset, our high AC helps a lot, and strap a Fungi Tunic on and a monk can take yellows &amp; reds with ease at 30th level (probably higher, but 30 is how high my little iksar twink is : )<br>
<br>
  Oh, and at 60th level with reasonably good equipment I make about a blue every 10 minutes soloing.  More if I can bum Aego / Focus from someone. <p><image src=http://homepages.paradise.net.nz/lpb/laokesig2.jpg></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ulaoke.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Laoke</A> at: 5/31/02 6:12:13 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/udewstreehugger.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dewstreehugger</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 541<br> <font color=#E9D756>(5/31/02 6:37:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9801.topic&index=29>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How do YOU solo?</span><hr size=1> With my Druid I just root dot. Root, epic, winged, click bracer. Can kill almost non stop.<br>
