<br>
As my monk, its that overpowering thing, I don't have a fungi and downtime becomes horrendous, but between bandaids and mend its workable...<br>
<br>
Bard... woo, you guys got it good, providing you can run around, something you do very well. (I had a bard, got too boring..)<br>
Anyway, if your kiting, Use your 3 dots and snare song, providing you have SoW. if you DONT have SOW/Jboots, use the 3 dots and twist Selo's in there. It doesn't truly matter how many dots get in there as long as the mob isn't handing you your ass. (Hint: Keep selo's going!) This becomes easier with that one selo's song that lasts 2 minutes.. or whatever..<br>
<br>
If you have your brass skill up high enough, or have singing steel legs, use the fear-kite method. Snare/fear/melee/dot/dot/haste rinse repeat.. This is how you see bards and rogues becoming decent teams.<br>
 If you have mana, you can charm/kite. Do the same as the dots but keep a mob charmed. This becomes difficult UNLESS your Wind(?) instrument skill is high enough, as charm uses 20 mana a pop (the 39+ one) and that adds up over 200 missed notes.<br>
Bards don't get root, but I believe that next to necro they are one of the most efficient Solo classes.<br>
<br>
 <p><font face="Arial" size=2 color="#0000CF"> Monk of Inferno's Hand</font><br>
<img src="http://216.122.116.150/images/triff/Wintafreshh_9.jpg" alt="No more sucky-sucky, sorry kids"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uiso101.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Iso101</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 202<br> <font color=#E9D756>(6/1/02 7:02:09 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9801.topic&index=35>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: sleep</span><hr size=1>  ME is my current home for soloing, root rotting is fine if I'm distracted with tells or the mobs have a lot of hps to get through. Personally I prefer to charm a ravenous beast, give it weapons, cast savage spirit on it and (keeping it snared between charms is the trick here) let it rip apart whatever comes by.<br>
<br>
 Quad kiting tends to become hex, oct or even deca-kiting with people training (yes I mean you Elaen!), but with c3 its fun anyway and you can always root off the ones you don't want and camp out to clear aggro. I can quad the vampires and goranga scouts with c3 without too many problems- crits on my AE go as high as 1624 per mob so they usuall drop fast- and switching to root/epic on the last couple of baddies is a nice way to start mana recoup.<br>
<br>
 XP, well I usually get a blue bubble per quad, obviously this can be higher if im kiting the 55+ mobs or have several adds. A nice way to supplement the xp is to pull three scouts or vampires and fill the fourth slot twice with a lesser blue mob. With pet kiting the xp is about the same, it just means I cant go afk for every long for fear of being eaten by my pet :)<br>
<br>
If your pet gets really low on health just click hide to break charm and lockdown everything with root; epic rot the enemy until the pet has hps again and recharm. Can even log out after a fight to clear aggro on the pet- unaggrod mobs regen a lot faster and you can just resnare/charm when its healthy again.<br>
<br>
One problem is that if you do zone from a train your pet will still have its aggro list so if you zone back and recharm it you will train yourself again.<br>
<br>
 Wouldn't advise quad kiting or pet kiting if you have a dodgy connection though- died so many times a few weeks back through a run of lag spikes.<br>
<br>
 Keep regen up, keep an eye out for other people-letting them aggro your mobs can be a nuisance for them and creates hassle keeping the mobs close together for AEs; plus people train continually in ME just to cross the zone. <p><DIV ALIGN="CENTER"><HR  SIZE="5" WIDTH="52%"> <STRONG> Isobella Turbokite ™</Strong> <BR> <EM>'Nuclear Embrace' </EM> <BR>  <HR  SIZE="5" WIDTH="52%"> <BR> <IMG SRC="http://members.madasafish.com/~egolectric/thundicon.gif" WIDTH="102" HEIGHT="50" ALIGN="CENTER"></DIV>
